start up k3s cluster with: 
sudo systemctl start k3s

default kubeconfig found here:
sudo cp /etc/rancher/k3s/k3s.yaml ~/.kube/config

test and get node name with:
kubectl get nodes

Following needed to set label on the node so that some pods will load on it
kubectl label nodes NODENAME node-role.kubernetes.io/worker=
kubectl label nodes NODENAME node-role.kubernetes.io/database=

Need to apply the k8s secret key so that encrypted secrets have the right key to decode:
kubectl apply -f k8s_privatekey.yaml

Start up argocd:
kubectl create -k ~/reclaim-the-stack/platform/6U8PyffjYadpXaSdgMWIzA8OLy933eLlaqGyjs3cplx4FvAgBVgc5wzVK5xQ06yj6mFrw5yHTt0EPOJLTcDK1Xx2kO8585opllrRiCzl3gf30

Load applications:
kubectl create -f argocd-root.yaml

argo password:
kubectl -n argocd get secret argocd-initial-admin-secret -o yaml | yq '.data.password | @base64d'
kubectl port-forward services/argocd-server -n argocd 8080:443